<br>
<br>
Just like any other spell we get there are uses for this and there are times WHEN to use it and times when NOT to use it. I love all the people pissing and moaning about if they get hit with an AE, then they are as good as dead. If you are in a situation where you might get hit with an AE, maybe you shouldn't have our little buddy up? <br>
Do you cast teleport constantly? Do you cast manaskin every 5 seconds? Do you chaincast IC on every mob you see? I am guessing, for most wizards, the answer is a resounding no, unless you are a ranger trying to play wizard. <br>
Ok, with that straight, it is probably not a good idea to have the familiar up ALL the time. If you truely are a wizard with high &quot;INT,&quot; then the idea of when to use the familiar and when not to will not be that big of a concept to grasp...<br>
<br>
<br>
